latestPosts.caption:
Sometimes, the universe has a bigger plan. Srishti shares a journey that began with a childhood dream, navigated rejection, and led to a moment she’ll never forget. 

“When I found out I’d be performing at Spoken Fest, I was ecstatic! I instantly knew I wanted to tell this story. In that moment, I couldn’t help but wish that my performance would fall on the 5th of March — the day my grandfather was born, and the day I received THE LETTER.

It’s incredible how the universe, or energies, or God, or whatever it is that guides us, works in such mysterious ways. The team at Spoken Fest unknowingly chose to release my performance on the very 5th of March. (WHAT?!!!)

This is more than just a performance — it’s a love letter to my grandfather, to myself, and to the divine. To the magic of this sacred day, when everything feels aligned.
To the magic of 5th of March.” 

Watch the full video on YouTube now!

🎥 Shot by: Slip Disc Films 
✂️ Edited by: Shannon Maben 

#Storytelling #HindiStorytelling #EnglishStorytelling #SpokenWord #SpokenFest #KommuneIndia #SpokenFestMumbai2025 #GulaboSitabo #AmitabhBachchan

It was the 5th of March, at around 6pm, the doorbell rang. 
My mother started screaming my name out and I ran to her to see what happened. 
She said ‘सृष्टि, अमिताभ बच्चन के घर से letter आया है’ It was surreal! Thank you @amitabhbachchan sir, for being the actor you are. For being the man you are. I am very lucky that I got to work with you and witness you perform in front of my eyes. 
And thank you to @shoojitsircar, @juhic3 and @jogifilmcasting for giving me Guddo!❤️ And @ayushmannk, Vijay Raaz and Bijendra Kaala for making this a memory of a lifetime. 🧜🏻‍♀️🧜🏻‍♀️🧜🏻‍♀️
